1747 - Lower the opacity on text and chevrons of disabled items to correspond with their lighter icon. r=johannh, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2QaD8wG1A6Y", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI.inc.css", "browser/themes/shared/toolbarbuttons.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa864d51aa9b08944ace50ed9dfdc2616e8cb473", "parents": ["b5ec72ee69fbe442c47b996d4b65282123c66795"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1413295 - Use BrandShortName as the title for new shortcuts, and rename existing shortcuts our installer created. r=rstrong, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: K4YvG5DZgqb", "files": ["browser/installer/windows/nsis/installer.nsi", "browser/installer/windows/nsis/shared.nsh", "toolkit/mozapps/installer/windows/nsis/common.nsh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "90ef9d0bc2ad54527f4a8ef2f73e2ecb052b0da8", "parents": ["aa864d51aa9b08944ace50ed9dfdc2616e8cb473"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Fred Lin \u003cgasolin@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1412164 - Add tour_type and timestamp column for onboarding telemetry. r=Fischer, r=liuche, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: aqeoxjR7Tu", "files": ["browser/extensions/onboarding/OnboardingTelemetry.jsm", "browser/extensions/onboarding/content/onboarding.js", "browser/extensions/onboarding/data_events.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "77b37cb80401a017381b436f8b87ffa86b6bb920", "parents": ["90ef9d0bc2ad54527f4a8ef2f73e2ecb052b0da8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1413478 - Fix styling of snapshot delete button in memory tool. r=gregtatum, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FbAWplGGR1", "files": ["devtools/client/memory/components/snapshot-list-item.js", "devtools/client/themes/memory.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "84fdf0a6465716f5a85f879792b7cda9fea5a13c", "parents": ["77b37cb80401a017381b436f8b87ffa86b6bb920"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1413568 - Update installer icons. r=mconley, a=ritu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1KJWrbZGglW", "files": ["other-licenses/7zstub/firefox/7zSD.sfx", "other-licenses/7zstub/src/7zip/Bundles/SFXSetup-moz/setup.ico"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "48d9303105bdc1a6b734a39146c90668ab56001d", "parents": ["84fdf0a6465716f5a85f879792b7cda9fea5a13c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eden Chuang \u003cechuang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1413056 - Use utils.js in test_bug1408734.html for waitForState and waitForControlled. r=bkelly, a=test-only", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/test_bug1408734.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "de5b0fe8f4e556abb4f449809059758cf0b28be7", "parents": ["48d9303105bdc1a6b734a39146c90668ab56001d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1406505 - Fix element.getContainer() to return button as container. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nBecause as long as bug 1089326 is not fixed child nodes of \u003cbutton\u003e\nare not part of the element tree. As such the button has to be returned\nas container for any of those nodes.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Jq6B9Kn7VAf", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_click.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7ce2c31171767b171236f3c5df5ff139ca1746b0", "parents": ["de5b0fe8f4e556abb4f449809059758cf0b28be7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1406505 - Fix element.isInView to use table cells instead of rows. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nAs long as bug 1413493 has not been fixed the \u003ctr\u003e nodes will not be part\nof the element tree. To workaround this problem we could use the first\nfound cell of the given row to check for visibility.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 57nuvxYrSMg", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_click.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d4ede1341fbf5e29437c6d7c1ebf60b01592ddb5", "parents": ["7ce2c31171767b171236f3c5df5ff139ca1746b0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1406505 - Improve click tests for both legacy and wdspec compliant clicks. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nSome of the tests do not check if the click() was successful. To prove that\nthe click methods work, such a check always has to happen.\n\nAlso some tests should be executed in both the legacy and webdriver compliant\nmode to ensure there are no regressions. Affected tests have been moved around.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Lr2TMpJHLW5", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_click.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4cab93886f10fc1a5e65bbbd60d5dbbe9aa4a9ca", "parents": ["d4ede1341fbf5e29437c6d7c1ebf60b01592ddb5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1413821 - Skip final assertion in test_inclusive_descendant for Android. a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7fadvwbofPb", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_click.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6cf9fe9ff66d8e2188ad384d617585560412a5bb", "parents": ["4cab93886f10fc1a5e65bbbd60d5dbbe9aa4a9ca"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Cooper \u003cmcooper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1413643 - Sync shield recipe-client v76.1 from Github (commit 10b351b). r=rhelmer, a=ritu on a CLOSED TREE\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FBP54WWP00S", "files": ["browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/bootstrap.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/install.rdf.in", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/lib/PreferenceExperiments.jsm", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser_PreferenceExperiments.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/test/browser/browser_bootstrap.js", "browser/extensions/shield-recipe-client/vendor/LICENSE_THIRDPARTY"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8c3926699de4b2f03f13a93d3750deb445b64396", "parents": ["6cf9fe9ff66d8e2188ad384d617585560412a5bb"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_57_0b14_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_57_0b14_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_57_0b14_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1509646287, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "8117": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1413852 - TcpTransport.receive() doesn't obey current socket timeout. r=automatedtester, a=test-only\n\nThe getter for socket_timeout should always return the current socket\ntimeout from the socket instance first, and only fallback to the\nprivate property if no socket instance exists.\n\nThis ensures that all methods will always operate on the current\nsocket timeout value.\n\nAlso using a timeout of 2s for receiving the hello string might be too\nless for slow running builds. To prevent intermittent failures for\nstart_session, a good value might be 60s.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HywjFfClrRr", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/transport.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "92ee9c76e7f8d61c39288f662d2e99b2ddf63c38", "parents": ["8c3926699de4b2f03f13a93d3750deb445b64396"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1413852 - Improve failure message for socket connection attempts. r=automatedtester, a=test-only\n\nInstead of a general socket timeout failure indicate that no hello\ndata has been received through the socket right after the call to\nconnect().\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EPNiCLNyFFH", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/transport.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "15d000a84572ee314049f8afb6bef56478d8716a", "parents": ["92ee9c76e7f8d61c39288f662d2e99b2ddf63c38"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1204254 - Try to make test_devtools_serviceworker_interception.html handle --verify runs again. r=asuth, a=test-only", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/chrome.ini", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/fetch.js", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/test_devtools_serviceworker_interception.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/test_fetch_integrity.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/utils.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f444b8fb9ea9e76d4ba667894ea3014a6fc85cd1", "parents": ["15d000a84572ee314049f8afb6bef56478d8716a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "FIREFOX_57b_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1411746 - Make tests that wait for controller change also wait for SW activation before claim(). r=tt, a=test-only on a CLOSED TREE", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/test_fetch_integrity.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/test_unresolved_fetch_interception.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/unresolved_fetch_worker.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b7359840ec7621fa71413831aafbbaccd9d0613", "parents": ["f444b8fb9ea9e76d4ba667894ea3014a6fc85cd1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1509660065, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "8118": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Ratcliffe \u003cmratcliffe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412311 - DevTools Shared Components to ES6 classes r=nchevobbe\n\nIn devtools/client/shared/components/tree/TreeView.js I have had to leave defaultProps outside the getter as a temporary workaround for bug 1413167.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1yaxqFnC92p", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/components/AutoCompletePopup.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/Frame.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/HSplitBox.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/NotificationBox.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/SearchBox.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/SidebarToggle.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/StackTrace.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/Tree.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/splitter/Draggable.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/splitter/SplitBox.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/tabs/TabBar.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/tabs/Tabs.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/test/mochitest/test_tabs_menu.html", "devtools/client/shared/components/tree/LabelCell.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/tree/TreeCell.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/tree/TreeHeader.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/tree/TreeRow.js", "devtools/client/shared/components/tree/TreeView.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3fa859a78370f2df0639a63ba7accad45ff7f60a", "parents": ["083a5838f76a418779c2f4fc01152bc3be355fc0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1411460 - Sync input.css with style in textbox.css. r=dao\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 63Fl0jtMPXc", "files": ["editor/reftests/xul/input.css", "editor/reftests/xul/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "be60c2b625ae9a7c5d8711a70ac8722d936b1f27", "parents": ["3fa859a78370f2df0639a63ba7accad45ff7f60a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1409727 - Expose the audio node recording pref to about:config. r=jib\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DbPH3umsH9v", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ea9eada6667e603021ada2e5e63005d6d110d0f5", "parents": ["be60c2b625ae9a7c5d8711a70ac8722d936b1f27"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1409727 - Add a mode and pref to disallow frame drops in MediaRecorder. r=SingingTree\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CJBJURDn7gB", "files": ["dom/media/encoder/MediaEncoder.cpp", "dom/media/encoder/TrackEncoder.h", "dom/media/encoder/VP8TrackEncoder.cpp", "dom/media/encoder/VP8TrackEncoder.h", "dom/media/gtest/TestVideoTrackEncoder.cpp", "dom/media/gtest/TestWebMWriter.cpp", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "baf693d2380daa0b704383e890281b1a0d81a575", "parents": ["ea9eada6667e603021ada2e5e63005d6d110d0f5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410829 - Signal listeners removed on shutdown so they can clean up. r=padenot\n\nWhen shutting down we shut modules down in the order of\n[media, gfx, cycleCollector].\n\nAt the same time we rely on destructors to clean up resources for MediaStreams\nand MediaStreamTracks, but these objects may be held until cycleCollector\nshutdown. Gfx resources are not allowed to be released after gfx shutdown, which\nis where we this approach hits a wall.\n\nThis patch will signal them through the three available listener types to clean\nup during media shutdown.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FwsG3ukV29P", "files": ["dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.cpp", "dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "db0fa983b90f44be14aa9b31257149aee28ea6b9", "parents": ["baf693d2380daa0b704383e890281b1a0d81a575"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410829 - Clean up streams and listeners before unblocking shutdown. r=padenot\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CcGaAJAUahm", "files": ["dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d9257f9b2296e23faf43594a4f3c1698003e6a2b", "parents": ["db0fa983b90f44be14aa9b31257149aee28ea6b9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410829 - Clear out mImage on media shutdown. r=jib\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 468prmnuwrk", "files": ["dom/media/CanvasCaptureMediaStream.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0253bbb60b2fc61bc4e32943dfcacde5f26e680a", "parents": ["d9257f9b2296e23faf43594a4f3c1698003e6a2b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Patrick McManus \u003cmcmanus@ducksong.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413831 - Make Some DNS Telemetry Opt-Out r=bagder\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1GcoNX5bipT", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/histogram-whitelists.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b23c3a2f8e9d752be559f568ec8168b1ecf5577c", "parents": ["0253bbb60b2fc61bc4e32943dfcacde5f26e680a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luke Chang \u003clchang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413479 - [Form Autofill] A field with an empty string in the incoming record shouldn't be saved to storage. r=steveck\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Iwp05R4GS6X", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/ProfileStorage.jsm", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/test_addressRecords.js", "browser/extensions/formautofill/test/unit/test_creditCardRecords.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "57072e6ba78b252aeb7fbba3d6b9f4dcd55a66bb", "parents": ["b23c3a2f8e9d752be559f568ec8168b1ecf5577c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nevin Chen \u003ccnevinchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413114 - Enable full bookmark management features by default. r=jwu,maliu\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GgqloikZnF8", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/bookmarks/BookmarkUtils.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e1a4d0b5eb152db7d06ccd20f919879a440ab6db", "parents": ["57072e6ba78b252aeb7fbba3d6b9f4dcd55a66bb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413593 - Add win32 cross compilation config for geckodriver. r=jgraham\n\nWhen cross-compiling geckodriver for i686-pc-windows-gnu from Linux\nx86-64, this custom cargo configuration is needed.  It specifies\nthe linker to use as well as a rustc flag for disabling backtraces\non panic, as far as I gather.\n\nNeither of these options are necessary, of course, when we start\nreleasing geckodriver from Taskcluster, because we will then not\nrely on cross-compilation.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6q7wIBNrCHB", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/.cargo/config"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b89b4bc79c27daf844eee77a553369bdb8aa329", "parents": ["e1a4d0b5eb152db7d06ccd20f919879a440ab6db"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Franziskus Kiefer \u003cfranziskuskiefer@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401594 - land NSS NSS_3_34_BETA1 UPGRADE_NSS_RELEASE, r=me\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8ckNdJ29KWZ", "files": ["security/nss.symbols", "security/nss/TAG-INFO", "security/nss/automation/abi-check/expected-report-libnss3.so.txt", "security/nss/automation/abi-check/expected-report-libssl3.so.txt", "security/nss/automation/buildbot-slave/build.sh", "security/nss/cmd/certutil/certutil.c", "security/nss/cmd/lib/secutil.c", "security/nss/cmd/listsuites/listsuites.c", "security/nss/cmd/manifest.mn", "security/nss/cmd/rsapoptst/rsapoptst.c", "security/nss/cmd/rsapoptst/rsapoptst.gyp", "security/nss/coreconf/coreconf.dep", "security/nss/cpputil/cpputil.gyp", "security/nss/cpputil/databuffer.cc", "security/nss/cpputil/databuffer.h", "security/nss/cpputil/manifest.mn", "security/nss/doc/certutil.xml", "security/nss/doc/html/certutil.html", "security/nss/doc/html/pk12util.html", "security/nss/doc/nroff/certutil.1", "security/nss/doc/nroff/pk12util.1", "security/nss/doc/pk12util.xml", "security/nss/fuzz/tls_mutators.cc", "security/nss/gtests/cryptohi_gtest/Makefile", "security/nss/gtests/cryptohi_gtest/cryptohi_gtest.gyp", "security/nss/gtests/cryptohi_gtest/cryptohi_unittest.cc", "security/nss/gtests/cryptohi_gtest/manifest.mn", "security/nss/gtests/manifest.mn", "security/nss/gtests/pk11_gtest/manifest.mn", "security/nss/gtests/pk11_gtest/pk11_gtest.gyp", "security/nss/gtests/ssl_gtest/ssl_auth_unittest.cc", "security/nss/gtests/ssl_gtest/ssl_gtest.cc", "security/nss/gtests/ssl_gtest/ssl_keylog_unittest.cc", "security/nss/gtests/ssl_gtest/tls_agent.cc", "security/nss/gtests/ssl_gtest/tls_agent.h", "security/nss/lib/certdb/certdb.c", "security/nss/lib/ckfw/builtins/certdata.txt", "security/nss/lib/ckfw/builtins/nssckbi.h", "security/nss/lib/cryptohi/cryptohi.h", "security/nss/lib/cryptohi/keyi.h", "security/nss/lib/cryptohi/seckey.c", "security/nss/lib/cryptohi/secsign.c", "security/nss/lib/cryptohi/secvfy.c", "security/nss/lib/freebl/rsa.c", "security/nss/lib/nss/nss.def", "security/nss/lib/pk11wrap/pk11merge.c", "security/nss/lib/pk11wrap/pk11obj.c", "security/nss/lib/pk11wrap/pk11pub.h", "security/nss/lib/pk11wrap/secmodti.h", "security/nss/lib/pkcs7/p7create.c", "security/nss/nss.gyp", "security/nss/tests/all.sh", "security/nss/tests/cert/cert.sh", "security/nss/tests/cipher/cipher.sh", "security/nss/tests/common/init.sh", "security/nss/tests/pkits/pkits.sh", "security/nss/tests/ssl/ssl.sh", "security/nss/tests/ssl_gtests/ssl_gtests.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "100e006a2730f8a65aaebd14e30de3a055d9b46a", "parents": ["725d13675a52e997870c98bee564f9e04cdc62c6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Taubert \u003cttaubert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413598 - Pull in latest changes from u2f-hid-rs git repository r=jcj\n\nReviewers: jcj\n\nReviewed By: jcj\n\nBug #: 1413598\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D181", "files": ["dom/webauthn/u2f-hid-rs/.travis.yml", "dom/webauthn/u2f-hid-rs/src/windows/winapi.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4814fd8f7eede29b8249c83b3048dd4129d07df4", "parents": ["100e006a2730f8a65aaebd14e30de3a055d9b46a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Taubert \u003cttaubert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412408 - Fix content process leak of U2FTransactionChild instances r=jcj\n\nSummary:\nThis patch fixes the reported leak of U2FTransactionChild instances in the\ncontent process by introducing a WebAuthnTransactionChildBase class that both\nWebAuthnTransactionChild and U2FTransactionChild inherit from.\n\nThis base class is responsible for proper refcounting. In\nBackgroundChildImpl::DeallocPWebAuthnTransactionChild() we currently always\ncast to WebAuthnTransactionChild, that will work only for the WebAuthn API. We\ncan now cast to WebAuthnTransactionChildBase to make this work for U2F as well.\n\nReviewers: jcj\n\nReviewed By: jcj\n\nBug #: 1412408\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D179", "files": ["dom/u2f/U2FTransactionChild.cpp", "dom/u2f/U2FTransactionChild.h", "dom/webauthn/WebAuthnTransactionChild.cpp", "dom/webauthn/WebAuthnTransactionChild.h", "dom/webauthn/WebAuthnTransactionChildBase.cpp", "dom/webauthn/WebAuthnTransactionChildBase.h", "dom/webauthn/moz.build", "ipc/glue/BackgroundChildImpl.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3a5bfa2ffc9890b7db7c49d5eabd044c6c217e70", "parents": ["4814fd8f7eede29b8249c83b3048dd4129d07df4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413635 - Generate AllocKind enum automatically and include more information in the definition macro r=sfink", "files": ["js/src/gc/AllocKind.h", "js/src/gc/Allocator.cpp", "js/src/jsgc.cpp", "js/src/jsgc.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec967bb543146d82433dfea5bec356088fbef992", "parents": ["3a5bfa2ffc9890b7db7c49d5eabd044c6c217e70"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413635 - Give AllocKind enum a uint8_t base r=sfink", "files": ["js/src/gc/AllocKind.h", "js/src/gc/Cell.h", "js/src/gc/Nursery.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1d72b8f7f10aa5add2209b9a3b61b9f3ba1e2d55", "parents": ["ec967bb543146d82433dfea5bec356088fbef992"], "tags": []}, {"author": "sotaro \u003csotaro.ikeda.g@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1408490 - Re-enable dom/plugins/test/mochitest/test_bug1092842.html r=jmaher", "files": ["dom/plugins/test/mochitest/mochitest.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f7b7b510805eef3d86e884fc6c8ead9902894b5a", "parents": ["1d72b8f7f10aa5add2209b9a3b61b9f3ba1e2d55"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1083482 part 4 - Remove more self-hosting code. r=anba", "files": ["js/src/builtin/Iterator.js", "js/src/builtin/Utilities.js", "js/src/builtin/WeakMapObject.cpp", "js/src/builtin/WeakMapObject.h", "js/src/vm/GlobalObject.cpp", "js/src/vm/SelfHosting.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ad4e37c81f648b398f09fd1aaef90ff4b9839b6", "parents": ["f7b7b510805eef3d86e884fc6c8ead9902894b5a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1083482 part 5 - Clean up CloseIterator, remove UnwindIteratorForException. r=arai", "files": ["js/src/jit/BaselineIC.cpp", "js/src/jit/CodeGenerator.cpp", "js/src/jit/JitFrames.cpp", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.h", "js/src/jsiter.cpp", "js/src/jsiter.h", "js/src/proxy/CrossCompartmentWrapper.cpp", "js/src/vm/Interpreter.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "efaccf22b2533dc2f58382649c72de56e0545b3f", "parents": ["0ad4e37c81f648b398f09fd1aaef90ff4b9839b6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1083482 part 6 - Merge GeneratorObject and StarGeneratorObject. r=arai", "files": ["js/src/jit/BaselineIC.cpp", "js/src/vm/GeneratorObject.cpp", "js/src/vm/GeneratorObject.h", "js/src/vm/SelfHosting.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ad093cafc3034a9fc1b925a53e603306de36d5c", "parents": ["efaccf22b2533dc2f58382649c72de56e0545b3f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1083482 part 7 - Rename StarGenerator to Generator in self-hosted code. r=anba", "files": ["js/src/builtin/Generator.js", "js/src/jit/BaselineIC.cpp", "js/src/jit/BaselineIC.h", "js/src/jit/BaselineICList.h", "js/src/jscntxt.h", "js/src/vm/AsyncFunction.cpp", "js/src/vm/AsyncIteration.cpp", "js/src/vm/CommonPropertyNames.h", "js/src/vm/GeneratorObject.cpp", "js/src/vm/SelfHosting.cpp", "js/src/vm/SelfHosting.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "def80dfc06543c1fe60518bbb8d21a456bef9f01", "parents": ["0ad093cafc3034a9fc1b925a53e603306de36d5c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ANDREEA PAVEL \u003capavel@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland r=merge a=merge on a CLOSED TREE", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "d621d36932cd57a6267f1f7432fdf50c083e5db2", "parents": ["6b89b4bc79c27daf844eee77a553369bdb8aa329", "40a14ca1cf04499f398e4cb8ba359b39eae4e216"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #19096 - Avoid decoding XHR type=\"json\" responses as UTF-16BE/LE (from hsivonen:no-utf16-json); r=avadacatavra\n\nhttps://infra.spec.whatwg.org/#parse-json-from-bytes says to use\n\"UTF-8 decode\" rather than \"decode\", so UTF-16BE/LE BOM should\nnot be honored.\n\nCC @SimonSapin\n\n\u003c!-- Please describe your changes on the following line: --\u003e\n\n---\n\u003c!-- Thank you for contributing to Servo! Please replace each `[ ]` by `[X]` when the step is complete, and replace `__` with appropriate data: --\u003e\n- [x] `./mach build -d` does not report any errors\n- [x] `./mach test-tidy` does not report any errors\n- [ ] These changes fix #__ (github issue number if applicable).\n\n\u003c!-- Either: --\u003e\n- [x] There are tests for these changes OR\n- [ ] These changes do not require tests because _____\n\n\u003c!-- Also, please make sure that \"Allow edits from maintainers\" checkbox is checked, so that we can help you if you get stuck somewhere along the way.--\u003e\n\n\u003c!-- Pull requests that do not address these steps are welcome, but they will require additional verification as part of the review process. --\u003e\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: e64083ccc624cd508d4001c5456ac7e04aa049a6", "files": ["servo/components/script/dom/xmlhttprequest.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b95ef3233000cbee8c45135e801455293b5f9e2", "parents": ["d621d36932cd57a6267f1f7432fdf50c083e5db2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ANDREEA PAVEL \u003capavel@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to mozilla-inbound r=merge a=merge on a CLOSED TREE", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "91e6ad83776b015b3f8726fde7c4dbdf7bb3c4a0", "parents": ["def80dfc06543c1fe60518bbb8d21a456bef9f01", "40a14ca1cf04499f398e4cb8ba359b39eae4e216"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Schuster \u003cevilpies@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413900 - Remove unused JS capability macros. r=arai", "files": ["js/src/jsversion.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c1576d8e9cb791665849c94dcfb9d833f90da9a4", "parents": ["91e6ad83776b015b3f8726fde7c4dbdf7bb3c4a0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412007 - HttpChannelChild::SendDivertComplete must always be executed after SendDivertOnStopRequest, r=mayhemer", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http