fmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1299286 - Enable touchdown to start dragging on elements with touchdownstartsdrag attributes. r=kats\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8TL9VfY88ip", "files": ["widget/windows/nsWindow.cpp", "widget/windows/nsWindow.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "16b3860f4f841f12db5d6302f15fc4d44ee31572", "parents": ["059f6f6a4ef55c40674ece3d1da45702a0811a47"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1299286 - Add the touchdownstartsdrag attribute to customize mode elements. r=jaws\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LziDBjACA0", "files": ["browser/components/customizableui/CustomizeMode.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ab416cb2c8db72b0c153cebe7eac201d141f1ba4", "parents": ["16b3860f4f841f12db5d6302f15fc4d44ee31572"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414271 - Update webrender to commit 34f1e8ed19a19cb950deef89ee31c1cf3d442d22. r=jrmuizel\n\nAlso includes regenerated FFI header.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BwH36DHIvrc", "files": ["gfx/doc/README.webrender", "gfx/webrender/examples/scrolling.rs", "gfx/webrender/res/brush.glsl", "gfx/webrender/res/brush_image.glsl", "gfx/webrender/res/clip_shared.glsl", "gfx/webrender/res/cs_clip_border.glsl", "gfx/webrender/res/cs_clip_image.glsl", "gfx/webrender/res/cs_clip_rectangle.glsl", "gfx/webrender/res/prim_shared.glsl", "gfx/webrender/res/ps_hardware_composite.glsl", "gfx/webrender/res/ps_text_run.glsl", "gfx/webrender/src/box_shadow.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/clip.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/clip_scroll_node.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/clip_scroll_tree.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/device.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/frame.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/frame_builder.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/gpu_types.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/platform/windows/font.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/prim_store.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/profiler.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/record.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/render_task.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/renderer.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/texture_cache.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/tiling.rs", "gfx/webrender/src/util.rs", "gfx/webrender_api/src/display_item.rs", "gfx/webrender_api/src/display_list.rs", "gfx/webrender_bindings/webrender_ffi_generated.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37344344dc14041f0f0e13e47bd67ba65629eba1", "parents": ["ab416cb2c8db72b0c153cebe7eac201d141f1ba4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414271 - Update for API change in WR PR 1977. r=jrmuizel\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Hcnlj0uFHN3", "files": ["gfx/webrender_bindings/src/bindings.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "07f3e8fb81444735d1466dc5e8704c0c9d6a85fd", "parents": ["37344344dc14041f0f0e13e47bd67ba65629eba1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414271 - Update reftests from changes in WR PR 1961. r=jrmuizel\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8pjCxVSHKhM", "files": ["layout/reftests/box-shadow/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/css-break/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/svg/filters/css-filters/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d64ad9981d9bc5834c38c75128d8258c149772a3", "parents": ["07f3e8fb81444735d1466dc5e8704c0c9d6a85fd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1401958 - Remove browser_webconsole_copy_entire_message_context_menu.js; r=Honza.\n\nThe test already exists with a different name (browser_webconsole_context_menu_copy_entire_message).\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9NmXosnAVAi", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser.ini", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_copy_entire_message_context_menu.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4c387a97b26ed2c8eda0d013c03dddc6619b8d84", "parents": ["d64ad9981d9bc5834c38c75128d8258c149772a3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1408928 - Rename and enable browser_webconsole_closing_brackets.js in new console frontend; r=Honza.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EEwk0mSD5Rs", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser.ini", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_jsterm_autocomplete_extraneous_closing_brackets.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_closing_brackets.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dfe08f7ae8d9e55f3bf412f437a9afabe72e9589", "parents": ["4c387a97b26ed2c8eda0d013c03dddc6619b8d84"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thom Chiovoloni \u003ctchiovoloni@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414997 - Ensure extension storage sync initializes Kinto exactly once r=glasserc\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3vYEp4eqpJO", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionStorageSync.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_storage.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ea8ee7aee5b896c78de6fe8e500dcb0f93c273bc", "parents": ["dfe08f7ae8d9e55f3bf412f437a9afabe72e9589"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1410907 - Add CanRecord(Pre)Release data to nsITTelemetry r=Dexter\n\nWe're starting a shift towards talking about release/prerelease data instead of\nbase/extended collection. For now this is just a naming change.\n\nAt the same time, we can render these attributes read-only, which is nice.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IRuKpzLYW7i", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Telemetry.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Telemetry.h", "toolkit/components/telemetry/nsITelemetry.idl", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetryController.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eba518f10477b43db1677bbc6ef591309e427fed", "parents": ["ea8ee7aee5b896c78de6fe8e500dcb0f93c273bc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1410143 - Whitelist ipc_channel_error for crash pings data-r?rweiss r=gsvelto\n\nAt present it is difficult to determine whether a crash ping is from a\nshutdownkill or not. By including ipc_channel_error we will be able to figure\nthat out.\n\nWe also as a bonus get additional insight into ipc channel error types that\nlead to crashes.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FepLsSS2tAI", "files": ["toolkit/components/crashes/CrashManager.jsm", "toolkit/components/crashes/tests/xpcshell/test_crash_manager.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/data/crash-ping.rst", "toolkit/crashreporter/client/ping.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f4e2e8992d066900c8bcd4d76a39a45369a2c20a", "parents": ["eba518f10477b43db1677bbc6ef591309e427fed"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Robin Miller \u003cmill2540@msu.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1403686 - Crops screenshots to a region based on a selector.  r=jaws\n\nCan now crop screenshots properly, for basic cases.\nAlso changed behavior so that if different window types are given, the application exits.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CqmIJFufONw", "files": ["browser/tools/mozscreenshots/browser.ini", "browser/tools/mozscreenshots/browser_screenshots_cropping.js", "browser/tools/mozscreenshots/mozscreenshots/extension/Screenshot.jsm", "browser/tools/mozscreenshots/mozscreenshots/extension/TestRunner.jsm", "browser/tools/mozscreenshots/mozscreenshots/extension/lib/robot_center.png", "browser/tools/mozscreenshots/mozscreenshots/extension/lib/robot_upperleft.png"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fd1ee37cb15c9060e845f5df58eb210a465c10dd", "parents": ["f4e2e8992d066900c8bcd4d76a39a45369a2c20a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aaron Meese \u003cajmeese7@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #19137 - Update README.md (from ajmeese7:patch-1); r=jdm\n\n\u003c!-- Please describe your changes on the following line: --\u003e\n\nCorrected 64bit\n\n---\n\u003c!-- Thank you for contributing to Servo! Please replace each `[ ]` by `[X]` when the step is complete, and replace `__` with appropriate data: --\u003e\n- [ ] `./mach build -d` does not report any errors\n- [ ] `./mach test-tidy` does not report any errors\n- [ ] These changes fix #__ (github issue number if applicable).\n\n\u003c!-- Either: --\u003e\n- [ ] There are tests for these changes OR\n- [X ] These changes do not require tests because it is a README update\n\n\u003c!-- Also, please make sure that \"Allow edits from maintainers\" checkbox is checked, so that we can help you if you get stuck somewhere along the way.--\u003e\n\n\u003c!-- Pull requests that do not address these steps are welcome, but they will require additional verification as part of the review process. --\u003e\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 70bbb9bf940835f01d0fe87fc617c44a5556541c", "files": ["servo/README.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6f89184bae30f96bf7dcef1d6a18b53896274258", "parents": ["fd1ee37cb15c9060e845f5df58eb210a465c10dd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alessio Placitelli \u003calessio.placitelli@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1409323 - Allow to register new addon scalars for an existing category. r=chutten\n\nIf we attempt to register again an old dynamic scalar, check if the new\ndefinition makes it expired. If so, update the expiration state and propagate\nthe new \"expired\" scalar to the content proecesses.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: A2LFN1irw4i", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryScalar.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/collection/scalars.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/browser/browser_DynamicScalars.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetryScalars.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "93469c0e79b6a2251a71763806163bf9c69294dc", "parents": ["6f89184bae30f96bf7dcef1d6a18b53896274258"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rail Aliiev \u003crail@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415207 - Add http://archive.mozilla.org/ to funsize download whitelist r=sfraser\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LPNO4EjSvpb", "files": ["taskcluster/docker/funsize-update-generator/scripts/funsize.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2494fb8deeeb29142414deb24165f225d648144b", "parents": ["93469c0e79b6a2251a71763806163bf9c69294dc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1408334 - add form to subscribe to mozilla developer newsletter in about:devtools;r=nchevobbe\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JuJqNS3r6NH", "files": ["devtools/shim/aboutdevtools/aboutdevtools.css", "devtools/shim/aboutdevtools/aboutdevtools.xhtml", "devtools/shim/aboutdevtools/subscribe.css", "devtools/shim/aboutdevtools/subscribe.js", "devtools/shim/aboutdevtools/tmp-locale/aboutdevtools.dtd", "devtools/shim/jar.mn", "devtools/shim/locales/en-US/aboutdevtools.properties"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3a8295d1ff40d1778e41a1fa1e72cda7692575e0", "parents": ["2494fb8deeeb29142414deb24165f225d648144b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413195 - Vendor webdriver's dependencies through geckodriver r=jgraham\n\nThe webdriver crate's dependencies are accounted for through geckodriver's\nCargo.lock file, because the webdriver dependency is given by path.\n\nThis commit reverts 540273e5cf22 made in bug 1412037.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: F0q9bDN3pqd", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/vendor_rust.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "783faae49328b8da97d6ca70678eb147541dd913", "parents": ["3a8295d1ff40d1778e41a1fa1e72cda7692575e0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413692 - Extensions page actions are pinned to address bar again and again. r=mixedpuppy\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HrhYTNSwygH", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/ext-pageAction.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_pageAction_shutdown.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini", "browser/modules/PageActions.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "71a2c8b33ae0ba5be4152df25da0b035381289aa", "parents": ["783faae49328b8da97d6ca70678eb147541dd913"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Halberstadt \u003cahalberstadt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414894 - [tryselect] Don't install shell extensions when bootstrapping fzf for |mach try fuzzy|, r=armenzg\n\nCurrently the prompts don't make it clear enough that running fzf will mess with your\nshell settings. This means users could install it without realizing, forget and get\nconfused later on.\n\nRather than try to address this, it's simpler to always skip the shell extensions as\n|mach try fuzzy| doesn't need them anyway. The extensions are useful, but are better\ninstalled via something like |mach bootstrap| which can be tackled in a separate bug.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2kx7UGO5LJ0", "files": ["tools/tryselect/selectors/fuzzy.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f0b47601baec03c6841615488c87c438d5a11dfd", "parents": ["71a2c8b33ae0ba5be4152df25da0b035381289aa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Swan \u003caswan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1398762 Fix unparseable host permission warning r=mixedpuppy\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: B2YALdhEKJs", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/Extension.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f3fe7b47cdacd5e4c5e7d8e52511fe4a71956ffb", "parents": ["f0b47601baec03c6841615488c87c438d5a11dfd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415199: Move some logic for loading taskgraph kinds from mozbuild.mach_bootstrap to taskgraph. r=dustin\n\nThis fixes the fallout from the mach command not being updated for 69c60c8fc528d8d038e22a2ae62f5ff7b1131231.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7WZ8wW4gnCY", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/mach_commands.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/generator.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec6b9fda18680e405d9c65f4486c2b382d20bf23", "parents": ["f3fe7b47cdacd5e4c5e7d8e52511fe4a71956ffb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset ec6b9fda1868 (bug 1415199) for breaking gecko decision task. r=backout on a CLOSED TREE", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/mach_commands.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/generator.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7e57b7dbca99c6378534730d6b9ee2dbb4368714", "parents": ["ec6b9fda18680e405d9c65f4486c2b382d20bf23"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J.C. Jones \u003cjjones@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414198 - Include \u003cfunctional\u003e in nsNSSCertificate.h r=keeler\n\nWe've a report of a compilation error on a different system because\nstd::function was undefined.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2MboMUdLzHj", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/nsNSSCertificate.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9c4b0c5cb5fc9ae20d4a93309c41c902dc3fa45d", "parents": ["7e57b7dbca99c6378534730d6b9ee2dbb4368714"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Rouget \u003cme@paulrouget.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #19135 - do not pass new size to Resize event (from paulrouget:resize); r=mbrubeck\n\nIt's not necessary to pass the new size to the resize event as it can be retrieved via `WindowMethods::framebuffer_size()`.\n\nFrom the perspective of the embedder, that makes things a bit easier.\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 9de76632f4e26721fac39d0903d290bb8de9775c", "files": ["servo/components/compositing/compositor.rs"