esc": "Bug 1414292 followup.  Indexed properties are enumerable on Window per spec, and thus we fix the CLOSED TREE.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6Q76VqwSiEx", "files": ["js/xpconnect/tests/mochitest/test_bug862380.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8e486e90b599027ed5d1edfc309639c17123a8c7", "parents": ["f9aafdff7559fb7da5c829d00c874623bf8db2d6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Margareta Eliza Balazs \u003cebalazs@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to mozilla-inbound. r=merge a=merge CLOSED TREE", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/test/mochitest/test_clear_form.html", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_autocomplete_crossdomain_iframe.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_autocomplete_in_debugger_stackframe.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_closing_brackets.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_copy_entire_message_context_menu.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/test-bug-989025-iframe-parent.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "3949da89d1c91ae3ffebe96fc3bdbb53762b58de", "parents": ["8e486e90b599027ed5d1edfc309639c17123a8c7", "40df5dd35fdb7ce3652fe4448ac8961c075c928e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Parks \u003cdparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1411631 - Use ContiguousEnumSerializerInclusive for GetOpenFileName IPC. r=jimm\n\nUse the new helper for serializing enums in IPDL.", "files": ["dom/plugins/ipc/PluginMessageUtils.h", "dom/plugins/ipc/PluginModuleParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e195ac70ab165bd6806d0bffc3db25fcdd708c51", "parents": ["3949da89d1c91ae3ffebe96fc3bdbb53762b58de"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicholas Nethercote \u003cnnethercote@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414096 - Remove support for nsISupportsString values in nsPrefBranch::{get,set}ComplexValue(). r=florian.\n\nBug 1345294 introduced nsPrefBranch::{get,set}StringPref(), which allowed the\ngetting of utf8 strings from prefs, which previously required using\nnsISupportsString with {get,set}ComplexValue. That bug also converted most\nuses.\n\nThis patch finishes the job.\n\n- It removes the nsISupportsString support.\n\n- It converts existing code that relied on the nsISupportsString.\n\n- It removes the lint that was set up to detect such uses of nsISupportsString.", "files": ["mobile/android/chrome/content/about.js", "modules/libpref/Preferences.cpp", "modules/libpref/nsIPrefBranch.idl", "modules/libpref/test/unit/test_defaultValues.js", "modules/libpref/test/unit/test_libPrefs.js", "netwerk/dns/nsIDNService.cpp", "testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/marionette.py", "toolkit/content/tests/chrome/test_preferences.xul", "toolkit/modules/Preferences.jsm", "toolkit/modules/Troubleshoot.jsm", "toolkit/modules/tests/xpcshell/test_Preferences.js", "tools/lint/docs/linters/eslint-plugin-mozilla.rst", "tools/lint/eslint/eslint-plugin-mozilla/lib/configs/recommended.js", "tools/lint/eslint/eslint-plugin-mozilla/lib/index.js", "tools/lint/eslint/eslint-plugin-mozilla/lib/rules/avoid-nsISupportsString-preferences.js", "tools/lint/eslint/eslint-plugin-mozilla/package.json", "tools/lint/eslint/eslint-plugin-mozilla/tests/avoid-nsISupportsString-preferences.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e843de356b7e5f3cb01f114bc101f4a71092550b", "parents": ["e195ac70ab165bd6806d0bffc3db25fcdd708c51"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backout a3785ec9a48c / bug 1410276 on request from pbone - Add a canary field to nsStringBuffer. r=backout", "files": ["xpcom/string/nsStringBuffer.h", "xpcom/string/nsSubstring.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "23f86a1ac424051004163f370b80d7b7bc5a35dd", "parents": ["e843de356b7e5f3cb01f114bc101f4a71092550b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415086 - Fixing a out-of-scope issue for a string in Worklet code, r=qdot", "files": ["dom/worklet/Worklet.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "90a7bc300af375c80574266857e3ce46c30c6697", "parents": ["23f86a1ac424051004163f370b80d7b7bc5a35dd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1411627 - Stop sending sticky clips to WR for scrollframes with no ASR. r=mstange\n\nIf the scrollframe has no ASR and is not async scrollable, WR will never\nneed to adjust the position of the sticky item. So we don't actually\nneed to send this data to WR. In theory this would be harmless but the\nlater patches in this bug actually expose another coordinate space\nmismatch between the gecko and WR sticky-position code, so this patch is\nneeded to avoid the latent problem from manifesting to the user.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: J0LMcU1FudA", "files": ["layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a165d1dcc9049d07a7fd4368838be162bbcf54ed", "parents": ["ee8c2f65351c596cbbfbdea5b86562ce11d2c1e2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1411627 - Send the applied offset for sticky frames to WR. r=mstange\n\nThere are cases where we do a main-thread paint at a scroll position\nwhere sticky offsets have been applied in order to keep sticky items\nvisually unmoving. From that paint, it's possible to do an async-scroll\nin the direction that reduces the sticky offset. In order for WR to\nhandle this case properly we need to tell WR how much of a sticky offset\nwas already applied on the main thread.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 79DsfPpsIfA", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderLayersLogging.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderLayersLogging.h", "gfx/webrender_bindings/WebRenderAPI.cpp", "gfx/webrender_bindings/WebRenderAPI.h", "gfx/webrender_bindings/src/bindings.rs", "gfx/webrender_bindings/webrender_ffi_generated.h", "layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "857a0e87e490abaab3595ed0cbb5a5d969860772", "parents": ["a165d1dcc9049d07a7fd4368838be162bbcf54ed"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1411627 - Add reftests. r=mstange\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: apbFCe2uzF", "files": ["layout/reftests/async-scrolling/reftest.list", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/sticky-pos-scrollable-4-ref.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/sticky-pos-scrollable-4.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/sticky-pos-scrollable-5-ref.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/sticky-pos-scrollable-5.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/sticky-pos-scrollable-6-ref.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/sticky-pos-scrollable-6.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6ca404d46fc283ec150c7ecfc7197415910d3fb2", "parents": ["857a0e87e490abaab3595ed0cbb5a5d969860772"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415199: Move some logic for loading taskgraph kinds from mozbuild.mach_bootstrap to taskgraph. r=dustin\n\nThis fixes the fallout from the mach command not being updated for 69c60c8fc528d8d038e22a2ae62f5ff7b1131231.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7WZ8wW4gnCY", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/mach_commands.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/generator.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/test/test_generator.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e605cf1f7c60c4dd0c072d17e628a9b6297a15f7", "parents": ["6ca404d46fc283ec150c7ecfc7197415910d3fb2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1339329 - cert error time warnings should only appear for recent blocklists and if clock skew is sufficient to make cert valid, r=johannh\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6HvOnc54edi", "files": ["browser/base/content/content.js", "browser/base/content/test/about/browser_aboutCertError.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3681cc015ec7894e50304f2a1239b98b7c886a9c", "parents": ["e605cf1f7c60c4dd0c072d17e628a9b6297a15f7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Comella \u003cmichael.l.comella@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415266: Enable Pocket by default. r=liuche\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CJXNQpsYTf6", "files": ["mobile/android/app/src/main/res/values/bool.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "78be743420f1baa228dee39b59aeb4dc36505d5c", "parents": ["3681cc015ec7894e50304f2a1239b98b7c886a9c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415152: No need for AdjustAppendForAfter, since ::after is handled in FindNextSibling. r=mats\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5jfJul3cJj3", "files": ["layout/base/nsCSSFrameConstructor.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2ff9e05a7dfe7298e718a734ed3472cf0b611c86", "parents": ["78be743420f1baa228dee39b59aeb4dc36505d5c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Halberstadt \u003cahalberstadt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414514 - [mochitest] Dump http status when failing to load test manifest, r=jmaher\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4yRSWa1m0Kt", "files": ["testing/mochitest/manifestLibrary.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9cc431483c616fdcc2af815bcb2b34a2526100dc", "parents": ["2ff9e05a7dfe7298e718a734ed3472cf0b611c86"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Josh Matthews \u003cjosh@joshmatthews.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #16946 - Add intermittent failure reporting to filter-intermittents (from jdm:report); r=Manishearth\n\nWe need to address https://github.com/servo/saltfs/issues/671 before this can be enabled by default on the builders, but I got the pieces working locally. This collects relevant information about each recorded intermittent failure encountered during a test run and posts them to a webapp which stores them in a database for later investigation. This will allow us to track over time which intermittent test failures are the most frequent, as well as whether they only happen on a particular builder or operating system.\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 693c3dcfb29ecc2aa4610aabc68ce7381bfd5d87", "files": ["servo/etc/ci/buildbot_steps.yml", "servo/python/servo/testing_commands.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "26a70922efd74a004f2f2c5f0d1e2d35481ae554", "parents": ["9cc431483c616fdcc2af815bcb2b34a2526100dc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nico Grunbaum", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1377420 - add RID check in RTP in simulcast mochitests r=drno\n\n* Added RTP parser\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: B31iK4cDpOQ", "files": ["dom/media/tests/mochitest/mochitest.ini", "dom/media/tests/mochitest/parser_rtp.js", "dom/media/tests/mochitest/test_peerConnection_simulcastOffer.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b6fc02a83622688d72dc9183dacc239fd6317e93", "parents": ["26a70922efd74a004f2f2c5f0d1e2d35481ae554"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Nguyen \u003cntim.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414512 - Refactor ext-theme.js to have per-theme Theme objects and global tracking variables. r=mixedpuppy\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7omIglzvjsF", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/ext-theme.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/browser/browser.ini", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_themes_dynamic_getCurrent.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_themes_getCurrent_differentExt.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "858a5f9806c374c4136fe54168d9525eb13edffc", "parents": ["b6fc02a83622688d72dc9183dacc239fd6317e93"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Keeler \u0