ch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415414 - Make DeleteRangeTransaction::CreateTxnsToDeleteBetween() and DeleteRangeTransaction::CreateTxnsToDeleteContent() use RawRangeBoundary as their arguments r=m_kato\n\nBy the fix of bug 1407352, DeleteRangeTransaction::CreateTxnsToDeleteBetween()\nstarts to use child node instead of a set of container node and offset in it.\nHowever, this is ugly and using RawRangeBoundary may reduce computing offset\nmore.  So, they should use RawRangeBoundary to refer delete points.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: pwDHOxpz0E", "files": ["editor/libeditor/DeleteRangeTransaction.cpp", "editor/libeditor/DeleteRangeTransaction.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2d6c76ecff8dcb7cfce961885e7e0fa2f1b608c3", "parents": ["14e4883dc59825c0e30a482d1903ad87aff4afdd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412559 - Make the \"confirm repost\" prompt tab modal. r=bz\n\nThis is done to prevent malicious pages from abusing the feature\nto lock up the browser.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8Gf55nbMwCu", "files": ["docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "818860c42bcaa778c3c88bec897bc7bb1f417f3b", "parents": ["2d6c76ecff8dcb7cfce961885e7e0fa2f1b608c3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "tigercosmos \u003cb04209032@ntu.edu.tw\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #19161 - remove unused  script in `build_commands.py` (from tigercosmos:python2); r=emilio\n\n\u003c!-- Please describe your changes on the following line: --\u003e\ncode in `build_commands.py` duplicates with `openssl.makefile`, so it is unused.\n(It only use in openssl)\nhttps://github.com/servo/servo/blob/ae5dca985ee58fbcd18d7e470184beb2b7e3d547/python/servo/build_commands.py#L268\nhttps://github.com/servo/servo/blob/ae5dca985ee58fbcd18d7e470184beb2b7e3d547/support/android/openssl.makefile#L9-L10\nhttps://github.com/servo/servo/blob/ae5dca985ee58fbcd18d7e470184beb2b7e3d547/support/android/openssl.sh#L83-L84\n\n---\n\u003c!-- Thank you for contributing to Servo! Please replace each `[ ]` by `[X]` when the step is complete, and replace `__` with appropriate data: --\u003e\n- [X] `./mach build -d` does not report any errors\n- [X] `./mach test-tidy` does not report any errors\n- [ ] These changes fix #__ (github issue number if applicable).\n\n\u003c!-- Either: --\u003e\n- [ ] There are tests for these changes OR\n- [ ] These changes do not require tests because _____\n\n\u003c!-- Also, please make sure that \"Allow edits from maintainers\" checkbox is checked, so that we can help you if you get stuck somewhere along the way.--\u003e\n\n\u003c!-- Pull requests that do not address these steps are welcome, but they will require additional verification as part of the review process. --\u003e\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 1d6b8a5448f4a7b55e224b4d1fd4520b74095864", "files": ["servo/python/servo/build_commands.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9d38c74d5ffdb4353f36ad10a65681d492d340c", "parents": ["818860c42bcaa778c3c88bec897bc7bb1f417f3b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415835 - Convert xpcshell-tests in toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks to Bookmarks.jsm API. r=mak\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3HB47rMkpuy", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks/test_395593.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks/test_448584.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks/test_458683.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks/test_818584-discard-duplicate-backups.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks/test_818587_compress-bookmarks-backups.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks/test_818593-store-backup-metadata.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks/test_992901-backup-unsorted-hierarchy.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks/test_997030-bookmarks-html-encode.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/bookmarks/test_savedsearches.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cf6c386ae59c4d5a8120eddaf06e69ba6996dc49", "parents": ["b9d38c74d5ffdb4353f36ad10a65681d492d340c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Silverberg \u003cbsilverberg@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1381684 - Fix intermittent browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_tabs_lastAccessed.js, r=mixedpuppy\n\nThis patch introduces two changes to the test:\n\n1. It breaks apart the assertion that was combining three tests into individual assertions, so if this does\nfail again in the future it will be easier to spot the actual problem.\n\n2. It uses addTab and browserLoaded instead of openNewForegroundTab, which seems to allow the test to wait\nlong enough before starting the extension.\n\nWhen I was able to reproduce the failure, after separating the assertions, I found the one that was failing\nwas the check that tab2.lastAccessed was less than the current time. I believe that the current time was being\nrecorded too soon, which is why I changed the test to not record the current time until after both tabs have\ncompleted loading. This seems to fix the intermittent locally for me.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: I3VoYODwjgz", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_tabs_lastAccessed.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c908b2bffe6e8991ede42e196358e7db3041a9be", "parents": ["cf6c386ae59c4d5a8120eddaf06e69ba6996dc49"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Vincent Lequertier \u003cvi.le@autistici.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1381648 - Add non blocking time to the statistics panel of netmonitor; r=Honza\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Anw4hTlpPjH", "files": ["devtools/client/locales/en-US/netmonitor.properties", "devtools/client/netmonitor/src/components/StatisticsPanel.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bad9f2a1be214b9bc5277fe766fe0d5a7d146ad4", "parents": ["c908b2bffe6e8991ede42e196358e7db3041a9be"], "tags": []}, {"author": "dluca \u003cdluca@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland. a=merge on a CLOSED TREE", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "9aff6ae3fc566b7cb599b63b53350069801d83b5", "parents": ["bad9f2a1be214b9bc5277fe766fe0d5a7d146ad4", "2bdf6eed0f64a51dfe099e089852533595f1a896"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415225 - Remove dead code. r=jrmuizel\n\nThis code has been unused since the removal of layers-full WR codepaths.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JQn55Kbz5rr", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderLayerManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderScrollData.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderScrollData.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3cac8cc22a73b7dd5be823fdf59b97f9db72d612", "parents": ["9aff6ae3fc566b7cb599b63b53350069801d83b5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415225 - Stop setting the EventRegionsOverride flag on in-process subdocument layers. r=botond\n\nThe mechanics of this change is fairly straightforward - instead of setting the\noverride on the layer corresponding to the in-process subdocument, we just set\nthe flag on the display list builder; that flag is already checked when building\nthe layer event regions for descendant nsIFrames.\n\nAs a side-effect, we also don't need to force a layer for in-process subdocuments\njust because they have document-level APZ-aware listeners. One of reasons we were\ndoing so before was so that we would have a layer to stash the override flags on\nbut now we don't need that any more.\n\nNote that out-of-process subdocuments are not affected; for those cases\nthe nsSubDocumentFrame delegates BuildDisplayList to\nRenderFrameParent/nsDisplayRemote, which will still set the overrides on\nthe RefLayer that is created.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DZWglE4e62p", "files": ["layout/generic/nsSubDocumentFrame.cpp", "layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp", "layout/painting/nsDisplayList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ebd75f69dd52ea60272f91ee109b2100d786216c", "parents": ["3cac8cc22a73b7dd5be823fdf59b97f9db72d612"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415225 - Stop setting the EventRegionsOverride flag on root layers. r=botond,mattwoodrow\n\nAs with the previous patch, instead of setting the override on the root\nlayer, we set the flag on the nsDisplayListBuilder before building the\ndisplay list, and the flag automatically forces all event regions\ndisplay items to use their dispatch-to-content region instead of any\nother regions.\n\nBoth the WebRender and non-WebRender codepaths were setting the override\nflag on their root layers and don't need to any more.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1cz0ahqwkOm", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderCommandBuilder.cpp", "layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.cpp", "layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4cbed02f287828309cb63bc47f88bd0eb64a7893", "parents": ["ebd75f69dd52ea60272f91ee109b2100d786216c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415225 - Move the EventRegionsOverride field to be on RefLayers only. r=botond\n\nWe now set EventRegionsOverride flags on ref layers only, so\nthere's no need to have the APIs to set it on container layers in\ngeneral.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JKU4UXvdR2e", "files": ["gfx/layers/LayerMetricsWrapper.h", "gfx/layers/Layers.cpp", "gfx/layers/Layers.h", "gfx/layers/LayersTypes.h", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/LayerTransactionParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/LayersMessages.ipdlh", "layout/ipc/RenderFrameParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f92965e9eb3c8e74c780c6950eccf6b052352213", "parents": ["4cbed02f287828309cb63bc47f88bd0eb64a7893"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415225 - Small early-exit optimization. r=botond\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: A3UuqKKOsjA", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFrame.cpp", "layout/painting/nsDisplayList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "646849f41754096f072b2bae6c7c1b1b4999f9c0", "parents": ["f92965e9eb3c8e74c780c6950eccf6b052352213"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415225 - Add a couple of mochitests for event-regions overrides. r=botond\n\nThese two tests exercise the codepaths where an event regions override\nis set on (a) the root layer of a layer tree and (b) on an in-process\nsubdocument. I verified that case (b) was failing with webrender enabled\nwithout the patchset and passes now.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Kw6TQjNupSa", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/helper_override_root.html", "gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/helper_override_subdoc.html", "gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/mochitest.ini", "gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/test_group_overrides.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9d4871427e54e63213cf9e7b9647ff0fdd8d83cd", "parents": ["646849f41754096f072b2bae6c7c1b1b4999f9c0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Simon Sapin \u003csimon.sapin@exyr.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #19162 - Allow unused imports for AsciiExt in style code (from emilio:ascii-ext); r=emilio\n\nSee #19128, this part is cherry-picked so Gecko can build with rust nightly.\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: e7a654dd13f589e127193267bcb576ffd661c11d", "files": ["servo/components/selectors/attr.rs", "servo/components/selectors/parser.rs", "servo/components/style/attr.rs", "servo/components/style/counter_style/mod.rs", "servo/components/style/custom_properties.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/generated/pseudo_element_definition.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko/pseudo_element_definition.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/gecko_string_cache/mod.rs", "servo/components/style/properties/longhand/font.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/properties/longhand/pointing.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/str.rs", "servo/components/style/stylesheets/viewport_rule.rs", "servo/components/style/values/mod.rs", "servo/components/style/values/specified/align.rs", "servo/components/style/values/specified/angle.rs", "servo/components/style/values/specified/calc.rs", "servo/components/style/values/specified/grid.rs", "servo/components/style/values/specified/length.rs", "servo/components/style/values/specified/mod.rs", "servo/components/style/values/specified/percentage.rs", "servo/components/style/values/specified/text.rs", "servo/components/style/values/specified/time.rs", "servo/components/style_traits/viewport.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3242ac6fdb3879f723145e6b07fff04a5c960d1e", "parents": ["9d4871427e54e63213cf9e7b9647ff0fdd8d83cd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Maja Frydrychowicz \u003cmjzffr@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415694 - Test webdriver actions keyboard shortcuts; r=ato\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7izqD8JLoNv", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/MANIFEST.json", "testing/web-platform/tests/webdriver/tests/actions/key_shortcuts.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/webdriver/tests/actions/support/keys.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1f5a9447c57a5416fbe0aa062bd31810b0ee2ff0", "parents": ["3242ac6fdb3879f723145e6b07fff04a5c960d1e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Francesco Lodolo (:flod) \u003cflod@lodolo.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1396724 - Add plural rule for Shuar language to intl/locale/PluralForm.jsm r=Pike\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5HOVoaBHlGu", "files": ["intl/locale/PluralForm.jsm", "intl/locale/tests/unit/test_pluralForm.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b1f342836ba9405cb13714614c9e850f0bb1a29", "parents": ["1f5a9447c57a5416fbe0aa062bd31810b0ee2ff0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415845 - Enable two more clang-tidy checkers: misc-unused-using-decls & misc-argument-comment r=andi\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CXjGaqIdHan", "files": ["tools/clang-tidy/config.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1582c71d40d8502a38e09fccd0d5290bcaa45d0f", "parents": ["6b1f342836ba9405cb13714614c9e850f0bb1a29"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413522 - Use HiDPI icons on Windows for the toolkit warning and question icons, and lower the size of the icons on OSX so the HiDPI versions are not shown blurry. r=nhnt11\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8u3zxE9HiSx", "files": ["toolkit/components/prompts/content/commonDialog.css", "toolkit/components/prompts/content/commonDialog.js", "toolkit/components/prompts/content/commonDialog.xul", "toolkit/components/prompts/content/tabprompts.css", "toolkit/themes/linux/global/commonDialog.css", "toolkit/themes/linux/global/global.css", "toolkit/themes/osx/global/commonDialog.css", "toolkit/themes/osx/global/global.css", "toolkit/themes/windows/global/global.css", "toolkit/themes/windows/global/jar.mn"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a74c645411e7a93fd48ec1d4e17c4c771a2339a2", "parents": ["1582c71d40d8502a38e09fccd0d5290bcaa45d0f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414441 - Stop caching an XPConnect pointer in storage/. r=mak\n\nServices.h has a built in cache now\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 362qIrzf13F", "files": ["storage/mozStorageService.cpp", "storage/mozStorageService.h", "storage/mozStorageStatementJSHelper.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b98366a27c05e617771746cd10f1f685a1b82dff", "parents": ["a74c645411e7a93fd48ec1d4e17c4c771a2339a2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J. Ryan Stinnett \u003cjryans@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394841 - Check iframes for related tabs in WebExt. r=kmag\n\nWhen using WebExt messaging with Responsive Design Mode, message manager\nmessages traveling from content to parent such as \"MessageChannel:Messages\" are\nreceived with `event.target` set to the \u003ciframe mozbrowser\u003e inside RDM that\nhosts the content.\n\nHere we change `getSender` processing for messages like this to also check HTML\niframes for related tabs, in addition to XUL elements as before.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3qphe2W8jHM", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/ext-browser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4aa421a32de9a1bb122062ebec128cea5789baa8", "parents": ["b98366a27c05e617771746cd10f1f685a1b82dff"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J. Ryan Stinnett \u003cjryans@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394841 - Add WebExt messaging to RDM tunnel. r=ochameau\n\nWebExt messaging sends several new message types to content that should be\ntunneled by RDM.\n\nThis change allows them to reach content as expected in RDM mode.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GKelgOGBUKI", "files": ["devtools/client/responsive.html/browser/tunnel.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "134b46ce0aa580d9b181cc7d1ad3752fd7cc6460", "parents": ["4aa421a32de9a1bb122062ebec128cea5789baa8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J. Ryan Stinnett \u003cjryans@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1394841 - Test WebExt messaging with RDM. r=kmag,ochameau\n\nThis test verifies that WebExt messaging works as expected for both the\nbackground page scripts and content scripts when RDM is used.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3fODg3nYLr7", "files": ["devtools/client/responsive.html/browser/tunnel.js", "devtools/client/responsive.html/test/browser/browser.ini", "devtools/client/responsive.html/test/browser/browser_ext_messaging.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bbf3fb8a107c69674b02f187ad53908864407a37", "parents": ["134b46ce0aa580d9b181cc7d1ad3752fd7cc6460"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dale Harvey \u003cdale@arandomurl.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1385932 - Reenable browser_urlbar_search_reflows.js on Linux. r=mconley\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: H24TSQKemBp", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/performance/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d253ab30bac2ac8ab92e3cdd5bf89ba8073a4613", "parents": ["bbf3fb8a107c69674b02f187ad53908864407a37"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #19163 - style: Remove the skip_applying_damage \"optimization\" (from emilio:useless-opt); r=nox\n\nWe already remove all change hints down the tree when finding a reframe hint\nusing ClearServoRestyleFromSubtree in ServoRestyleManager, so this is useless.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1twx7iPt79x\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 20ccde9a75e52f3dc7adccf0136f5753deb41158", "files": ["servo/components/style/data.rs", "servo/components/style/matching.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "26c3f93ee76e0ca912948aabeee84a814dd58c15", "parents": ["d253ab30bac2ac8ab92e3cdd5bf89ba8073a4613"], "tags": []}, {"author": "dluca \u003cdluca@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 1 changesets (bug 1413522) for failing a11y on OS X  accessible/tests/mochitest/relations/test_ui_modalprompt.html r=backout on a CLOSED TREE.\n\nBacked out changeset a74c645411e7 (bug 1413522)", "files": ["toolkit/components/prompts/content/commonDialog.css", "toolkit/components/prompts/content/commonDialog.js", "toolkit/components/prompts/content/commonDialog.xul", "toolkit/components/prompts/content/tabprompts.css", "toolkit/themes/linux/global/commonDialog.css", "toolkit/themes/linux/global/global.css", "toolkit/themes/osx/global/commonDialog.css", "toolkit/themes/osx/global/global.css", "toolkit/themes/windows/global/global.css", "toolkit/themes/windows/global/jar.mn"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a7cfd60cb01ee1322a30786f48ae87b4f80b3208", "parents": ["26c3f93ee76e0ca912948aabeee84a814dd58c15"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J. Ryan Stinnett \u003cjryans@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415502 - Remove RDM browser-swap docs. r=jryans\n\nThese low level docs are getting out of date and causing confusion.  Further,\nthey are of limited value at this stage anyway.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FSoNniNZjtj", "files": ["devtools/client/responsive.html/browser/swap.js", "devtools/client/responsive.html/browser/tunnel.js", "devtools/client/responsive.html/docs/browser-swap.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c2e7d45a29a26698b5fe5976a39a9e001a2d68e5", "parents": ["a7cfd60cb01ee1322a30786f48ae87b4f80b3208"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreea Pavel \u003capavel@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge autoland to mozilla-central r=merge a=merge", "files": ["devtools/client/responsive.html/docs/browser-swap.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "cbebb4f65eeaea4ac12c8e22383f0a739d2ae429", "parents": ["6409f04e33d62148f988f567d1ef90a6f7b0ac9d", "c2e7d45a29a26698b5fe5976a39a9e001a2d68e5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreea Pavel \u003capavel@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge inbound to mozilla-central r=merge a=merge", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "277e2ae05f747e257eaa73e36f1bc31b98a21af9", "parents": ["cbebb4f65eeaea4ac12c8e22383f0a739d2ae429", "486620c2345ab558d0507c14a19e49f631b8347f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ffxbld", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug, Automated HSTS preload list update from host bld-linux64-spot-035 - a=hsts-update", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.errors", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7d84a639c2715e0278236c42a27486ae1fe79c4c", "parents": ["277e2ae05f747e257eaa73e36f1bc31b98a2