Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402283 - Rename extent_node_t fields. r=njn\n", "files": ["memory/build/mozjemalloc.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e2df7f0bf18245e0644b170a7b0173928da76afc", "parents": ["257e3b6e6cf823fa6a5b38dc4e68696f94acd0f6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402283 - Make arena_ralloc use the same arena as the original pointer when none is provided. r=njn\n\nWhen using plain realloc() on a pointer that was allocated with\nmoz_arena_malloc, we want the resulting pointer to still belong to the\nsame arena.\n", "files": ["memory/build/mozjemalloc.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3f44c449e280d5b1327028ccfdc0505070336209", "parents": ["e2df7f0bf18245e0644b170a7b0173928da76afc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402283 - Replace isalloc/isalloc_validate with static methods of a new AllocInfo class. r=njn\n\nBoth functions do essentially the same thing, one having more validation\nthan the other. We can use a template with a boolean parameter to avoid\nthe duplication.\n\nFurthermore, we're soon going to require, in some cases, more\ninformation than just the size of the allocation, so we wrap their\nresult in a helper class that gives information about an active\nallocation.\n", "files": ["memory/build/mozjemalloc.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6e0e82c6b316d742c9f92d96aa59198caa418499", "parents": ["3f44c449e280d5b1327028ccfdc0505070336209"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402283 - Associate an arena to each huge allocation. r=njn\n\nCurrently, huge allocations are completely independent from arenas. But\nin order to ensure that e.g. moz_arena_realloc can't reallocate huge\nallocations from another arena, we need to track which arena was\nresponsible for the huge allocation. We do that in the corresponding\nextent_node_t.\n", "files": ["memory/build/mozjemalloc.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a82bf86d86fd3d83da8a3d6e929533da52ea036e", "parents": ["6e0e82c6b316d742c9f92d96aa59198caa418499"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1402283 - Enforce arena matching on moz_arena_{realloc,free}. r=njn\n\nThis enforces the API contract as described in memory/build/malloc_decls.h.\n", "files": ["memory/build/Utils.h", "memory/build/malloc_decls.h", "memory/build/mozjemalloc.cpp", "memory/gtest/TestJemalloc.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ee9d4052e9493b3e8bca00f3bead8f1ea22b933b", "parents": ["a82bf86d86fd3d83da8a3d6e929533da52ea036e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415672 - Don't invalidate the entire frame tree when we're marking a specific frame as being modified. r=miko", "files": ["layout/painting/nsDisplayList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7129e7f79826bebb6cf13e9c11b63b7317a24773", "parents": ["ee9d4052e9493b3e8bca00f3bead8f1ea22b933b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413073 - Part 1: Add new crashtests for complex ASR cases. r=mstange", "files": ["layout/painting/crashtests/1413073-1.html", "layout/painting/crashtests/1413073-2.html", "layout/painting/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "08e3bd4e82de2f1306ec1739893fe089dde086dc", "parents": ["7129e7f79826bebb6cf13e9c11b63b7317a24773"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413073 - Part 2: Only force frames to have display items built if they intersect the dirty rectangle. r=mstange", "files": ["layout/painti