43271b7887c4a7fe246856ad0c857b215", "parents": ["87568918bedf2f2667b9254819af2d2daa637226"], "tags": []}], "date": 1511940078, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8257": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nes-AR -\u003e e542b02f422e\nes-CL -\u003e ed7233b876ad\nes-MX -\u003e 326cdf87fade", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e6c2d0a2584980cbec1ebc1f9527b0f7d80c9601", "parents": ["66eea4043271b7887c4a7fe246856ad0c857b215"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nes-AR -\u003e e542b02f422e\nes-CL -\u003e ed7233b876ad\nes-MX -\u003e 326cdf87fade", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8867b6c845b31adce11030301b8ddea6e7422f52", "parents": ["e6c2d0a2584980cbec1ebc1f9527b0f7d80c9601"], "tags": []}], "date": 1511943673, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8258": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug, Automated blocklist update from host bld-linux64-spot-307 - a=blocklist-update", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "54dac9f9c0429354e564cb6ef58b7fe3435ebf1d", "parents": ["8867b6c845b31adce11030301b8ddea6e7422f52"], "tags": []}], "date": 1511954155, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8259": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\noc -\u003e 2c9a8386f268", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9c16e62a2f500015f0c5309ac45db22533cb0bad", "parents": ["54dac9f9c0429354e564cb6ef58b7fe3435ebf1d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1511954491, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8260": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1420415 - TextEditor::CreateBRImpl() needs to make pointToInsertBrNode store mOffset before calling EditorBase::CreateNode() r=m_kato a=gchang\n\nWhen TextEditor::CreateBRImpl() splits a text node before inserting new \u003cbr\u003e\nelement, it initializes pointToInsertBrNode only with the right text node.\nThen, it refers its Offset() after inserting new \u003cbr\u003e node before the point.\nTherefore, the offset is computed with the new DOM tree.  So, adding 1 to\nthe offset is redundant only in this case.\n\nSo, before calling CreateNode(), it needs to make pointToInsertBrNode store\noffset with calling its Offset().\n\nNote that this ugly code will be replaced with patches for bug 1408227.\nAdditionally, this doesn't use AutoEditorDOMPointChildInvalidator because\nit's not available in 58 but we need to uplift this patch.\n\nFinally, I'm not sure how to check this in automated tests.  Therefore, this\npatch doesn't include automated tests.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IaQBonoGawR", "files": ["editor/libeditor/TextEditor.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3e16c8e2364ba5655325e2c4fa3df329db7a339b", "parents": ["9c16e62a2f500015f0c5309ac45db22533cb0bad"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1418747 - ContentCacheInParent needs to initialize mPendingCommitLength with 0 when it's created r=m_kato a=gchang\n\nContentCacheInParent::mPendingCommitLength is never initialized until it\nreceives eCompositionCommit(AsIs) event from widget or receives the latest\ncontent from the remote process when there is a composition.\n\nThe bug is, immediately after dispatching eCompositionStart and first\neCompositionChange event, MS Pinyin tries to query the character at caret,\nbut ContentCacheInParent::HandleQueryContentEvent() tries to resolve\nrelated position of an eQueryTextRect event with the uninitialized\nmPendingCommitLength.  Therefore, the query almost always fails and MS Pinyin\ngives up to show its candidate window.\n\nThis patch just initializes the member with 0.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JyYNqi8hoTa", "files": ["widget/ContentCache.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a9ce90a8eeabc58651c4e39c6a16be095865ac90", "parents": ["3e16c8e2364ba5655325e2c4fa3df329db7a339b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1417448 - Better use of monitors in NS_ReadInputStreamToBuffer, r=smaug a=gchang", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsNetUtil.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b4a737a2a3d7f56cace147a0fbaaf558b11a8f60", "parents": ["a9ce90a8eeabc58651c4e39c6a16be095865ac90"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Gaynor \u003cagaynor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1419811 - allow file content processes to access the com.apple.iconservices service; r=Gijs,haik a=gchang on a CLOSED TREE\n\nDirectory listing for file URLs needs access to draw icons for files.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KIEx00gB5ia", "files": ["security/sandbox/mac/SandboxPolicies.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "40a6d6c3807248bae0430bc57444a9aeaf0bbad3", "parents": ["b4a737a2a3d7f56cace147a0fbaaf558b11a8f60"], "tags": []}], "date": 1511964870, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8261": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mike Conley \u003cmconley@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1403563 - Allow multiple wheel events to accelerate scrollbox scrolling. r=dao a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Lo7HxK6TGwd", "files": ["toolkit/content/widgets/scrollbox.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a52371d2dadcdca0a7298054e06c6c0a7f7e4877", "parents": ["40a6d6c3807248bae0430bc57444a9aeaf0bbad3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1418810 - Use fallible assign to prevent OOM. r=mayhemer a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LU1RbkUIBZz", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsSimpleURI.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b863167623e2501ea0ca60c8b6a5d356add85a42", "parents": ["a52371d2dadcdca0a7298054e06c6c0a7f7e4877"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1417113 - CloneableWithRangeMediaResource InputStreamReader::Read must always return what has been read from the buffer, r=jya a=gchang\n\nBefore this patch, InputStreamReader::Read was returning NS_OK without updating\naRead if SyncRead() was unable to read the requested amount of data from the\nstream. Just because SyncRead() was executing in a do/while loop, we must\nalways update aRead with what was been read so far.", "files": ["dom/media/CloneableWithRangeMediaResource.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd498278dba7fa2a2b01938b489327bb14b6bcad", "parents": ["b863167623e2501ea0ca60c8b6a5d356add85a42"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Comella \u003cmichael.l.comella@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1416971: Update Pocket MORE link. r=liuche a=gchang on a CLOSED TREE\n\nUpdated URL is specified in comment 1.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3S6vJ4E7jYO", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/activitystream/homepanel/StreamRecyclerAdapter.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "af0fb48a0ac9614e26a528c3408ca0203c1069b5", "parents": ["cd498278dba7fa2a2b01938b489327bb14b6bcad"], "tags": []}], "date": 1511966289, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "dluca@mozilla.com"}, "8262": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": 