[]}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nast -\u003e f032cba8ac62\nkab -\u003e 0e63c4be8257\nor -\u003e 612c0849cf8e\npt-PT -\u003e 0ce727a47596\nur -\u003e 216b0658024e", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f7ff50f9a3b5d251093c2d5713009a4a1f04340d", "parents": ["f025ea4f1eb242094e70913f7e1417f143da26b1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1512228073, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8291": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nkab -\u003e 0d61939d0897", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5d258deb4e0170d101d3f36deb6e0e725a8774e4", "parents": ["f7ff50f9a3b5d251093c2d5713009a4a1f04340d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nkab -\u003e 0d61939d0897\nur -\u003e caeaf72a9536", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "87b9a23fc0cfc7b88f03f34f0533e5abb4dabe3d", "parents": ["5d258deb4e0170d101d3f36deb6e0e725a8774e4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1512231668, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8292": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tim Taubert \u003cttaubert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1413841 - Check for integer overflow in AesTask::DoCrypto(). r=keeler, a=gchang\n\nSummary:\nAfter calling mResult.SetLength(mData.Length() + 16) we should check that the\ninteger addition didn't overflow. It seems at the moment impossible to create\nArrayBuffers of size \u003e= 0x0xfffffff0, however adding a check here doesn't hurt.\n\nmResult.Length() is passed to the PK11 API functions as a maxOut parameter and\n/should/ be checked by the softoken crypto algorithm implementations. AES-ECB\nand AES-GCM seem to do that correctly.\n\nReviewers: keeler\n\nReviewed By: keeler\n\nSubscribers: mcote, ttaubert, jcj, keeler\n\nBug #: 1413841\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D188", "files": ["dom/crypto/WebCryptoTask.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9db3839609e097e84106c385e53ed12202d77f8a", "parents": ["87b9a23fc0cfc7b88f03f34f0533e5abb4dabe3d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1417439 - Release actors when message are pruned due to an MESSAGES_ADD action. r=Honza, a=gchang\n\nIn Bug 1371721, we created a new action to batch our message addition into the store. Which means that messages can be pruned when using this action,\nand implies releasing server actors.\n\nBut, at the moment, we only do that when we use the MESSAGE_ADD action.\nThis wasn't caught by tests because they explicitly use the MESSAGE_ADD action.\n\nThis patch makes the console release actors in reaction to a MESSAGES_ADD\naction and add a test to make sure we handle this as expected.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FfgvmKi9nM9", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/store.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/helpers.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/store/release-actors.test.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "35df0c984d4a2ba59a0eb16cbc073545ed13e80b", "parents": ["9db3839609e097e84106c385e53ed12202d77f8a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1421191 - In ConvolutionFilter::ComputeResizeFilter calculate the src pixel every loop iteration. r=lsalzman, a=gchang\n\nIf we try to be clever and increment by invScale then floating point inaccuracies can accumulate leaving srcPixel far off from where it should be.", "files": ["gfx/2d/ConvolutionFilter.cpp", "image/test/reftest/downscaling/1421191-1.html", "image/test/reftest/downscaling/1421191-1.png", "image/test/reftest/downscaling/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9e0f2dcb95f5966621c0ca8e446ebecb12d7e652", "parents": ["35df0c984d4a2ba59a0eb16cbc073545ed13e80b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luke Wagner \u003cluke@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415291 - Baldr: factor out ToTableIndex(). r=bbouvier, a=gchang", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmJS.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "70d5016333a434cb406e1714deb837bcafa07079", "parents": ["9e0f2dcb95f5966621c0ca8e446ebecb12d7e652"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brad Werth \u003cbwerth@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1421420 - Hold onto a weak reference to the grid container frame across reflow flushes triggered by devtools. r=dholbert, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2lkQr1jbnFd", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7649c04f02c36e8fc07c1e87637b1cea9f3ba823", "parents": ["70d5016333a434cb406e1714deb837bcafa07079"], "tags": []}], "date": 1512236108, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "8293": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrei Oprea \u003candrei.br92@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412265 - Font issues in the messages displayed for empty Highlights and Top Stories sections. r=ursula, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: B3t1wrXPTvG", "files": ["browser/extensions/activity-stream/css/activity-stream-linux.css", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/css/activity-stream-mac.css", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/css/activity-stream-windows.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a5ffba3f346184e9fbe361cc9e34bca257378ca6", "parents": ["7649c04f02c36e8fc07c1e87637b1cea9f3ba823"], "tags": []}, {