"366eae257e7e7d243149cc19096c18c3f15e8a32", "parents": ["d29b6af0d952625a6887082d1ab26e8eaeae3123"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Marco Bonardo \u003cmbonardo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415598. r=gijs, a=jcristau", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/History.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ff2ac648087a6f224cb5ed79663c016237a56cc2", "parents": ["366eae257e7e7d243149cc19096c18c3f15e8a32"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Boris Chiou \u003cboris.chiou@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1418806 - hashglobe: Dump more information if out of memory while allocating a table. r=emilio, a=jcristau\n\nThis is for Bug 1418806 and Bug 1416903. Sometimes, we got a crash message on stylo:\n\n\u003e  called `Result::unwrap()` on an `Err` value: FailedAllocationError {\n\u003e  reason: \"out of memory when allocating RawTable\" }\n\nbut this is not enough to debug, so let's add one more field in\nFailedAllocationError, so we can know the size we are allocating.\n\n---\n- [X] `./mach build -d` does not report any errors\n- [X] `./mach test-tidy` does not report any errors\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 7fd7c21c4c99dd9f8e118948f0c52d4b4073d559", "files": ["servo/components/hashglobe/src/lib.rs", "servo/components/hashglobe/src/table.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cc9318833c015f22f8bf57ff75e87bac07818761", "parents": ["ff2ac648087a6f224cb5ed79663c016237a56cc2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1512764316, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "8358": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset b3559b717873 (bug 1421313) for Android crashes.", "files": ["gfx/layers/LayerScope.cpp", "gfx/layers/moz.build", "gfx/layers/opengl/CompositorOGL.cpp", "gfx/layers/opengl/TexturePoolOGL.cpp", "gfx/layers/opengl/TexturePoolOGL.h", "gfx/la