 changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e e43ef66937d7\nid -\u003e 9f52d892ce32\nmy -\u003e 01b6308a62ac", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8ba7d2751512e8314593f5611005c8f4edcdec9e", "parents": ["e827926678c2bce27e5116555cf781cf215990a7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e e43ef66937d7\nbg -\u003e 0a93cb112cea\nid -\u003e 9f52d892ce32\nlv -\u003e f19528f177bb\nmy -\u003e 01b6308a62ac", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5b840d6589db2600932fccb36c04a2ac4f37e7bd", "parents": ["8ba7d2751512e8314593f5611005c8f4edcdec9e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1513599584, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8388": {"changesets": [{"author": "David Anderson \u003cdanderson@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Fix race condition when mapping a D2D surface while its DrawTarget mutates. (bug 1418348, r=bas) a=gchang", "files": ["gfx/2d/SourceSurfaceD2D1.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c843f2f3085e6439335e0fd5ad89eeb7f90ea7d5", "parents": ["5b840d6589db2600932fccb36c04a2ac4f37e7bd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412420 - Ensure upper bits are zeroed when calling a function that returns int32. r=nbp a=ritu", "files": ["js/src/irregexp/NativeRegExpMacroAssembler.cpp", "js/src/irregexp/RegExpStack.cpp", "js/src/irregexp/RegExpStack.h", "js/src/jit/CodeGenerator.cpp", "js/src/jit/MacroAssembler-inl.h", "js/src/jit/MacroAssembler.cpp", "js/src/jit/MacroAssembler.h", "js/src/jit/SharedIC.cpp", "js/src/jit/shared/CodeGenerator-shared.h", "js/src/jit/x86/CodeGenerator-x86.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b4d18da6b103eb83fffc14e0115434d2951c15e", "parents": ["c843f2f3085e6439335e0fd5ad89eeb7f90ea7d5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas B. Pierron \u003cnicolas.b.pierron@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1412653 - Distinguish between call stack used for outer resume points from call stacks used for resuming at one instruction. r=jandem a=ritu", "files": ["js/src/jit/IonBuilder.cpp", "js/src/jit/IonBuilder.h", "js/src/jit/MCallOptimize.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "935393b713cba967fa93f17358370a519b24e281", "parents": ["3b4d18da6b103eb83fffc14e0115434d2951c15e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1418966 - Pin TypeScripts better when doing Baseline debug mode OSR. r=bhackett a=ritu", "files": ["js/src/jit/BaselineCompiler.cpp", "js/src/jit/BaselineDebugModeOSR.cpp", "js/src/jit/IonAnalysis.cpp", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jsscript.h", "js/src/vm/EnvironmentObject.cpp", "js/src/vm/TypeInference-inl.h", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.cpp", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "32bb2e9efd3484064565dab8aa36fb5657db75c1", "parents": ["935393b713cba967fa93f17358370a519b24e281"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriele Svelto \u003cgsvelto@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1424304 - Workaround to allow the crashreporter to launch correctly on Fennec; r=ted.mielczarek a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EELVnTZF4Tv", "files": ["toolkit/crashreporter/nsExceptionHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "734cd1dab1a3f0d845a9e9e6c40ac575548a4b41", "parents": ["32bb2e9efd3484064565dab8aa36fb5657db75c1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425030: ia2Accessible::get_accessibleWithCaret: Gracefully handle null returned from SelectionManager::AccessibleWithCaret. r=surkov a=ritu\n\nWe weren't checking for null previously, thus causing a crash when there was no caret.\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6NNRafcVPhb", "files": ["accessible/windows/ia2/ia2Accessible.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e1b8647ff08e1b9529d146efb2134c6171c4cdae", "parents": ["734cd1dab1a3f0d845a9e9e6c40ac575548a4b41"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1424085 - add owning handles so cert references don't leak in IsCertificateDistrustImminent r=jcj a=lizzard\n\nnsIX509Cert::GetCert() returns a CERTCertificate whose reference count has\nalready been increased. Before this patch, when IsCertificateDistrustImminent\ncalled CertDNIsInList(rootCert-\u003eGetCert(), RootSymantecDNs) and\nCertDNIsInList(aCert-\u003eGetCert(), RootAppleAndGoogleDNs), the reference count on\nthose certificates would never get a corresponding decrement, so we would keep\nthose certificates alive until shut down. A reasonable and consistent solution\nis to introduce a UniqueCERTCertificate handle in each case to own the\nreference.\n\nThe status of this fix can be verified by setting MOZ_LOG=\"pipnss:4\", running\nFirefox, connecting to any host, and then shutting down. If an NSS resource\nreference has been leaked, \"[Main Thread]: E/pipnss NSS SHUTDOWN FAILURE\" will\nbe in the console output. Otherwise,\n\"[Main Thread]: D/pipnss NSS shutdown =====\u003e\u003e OK \u003c\u003c=====\" will be in the console\noutput.\n\nThis patch also removes nsIX509CertList::DeleteCert because it would also leak a\nreference. Luckily, nothing was using it.\n\nThis patch also clarifies the implementation of nsIX509CertList::AddCert by\nmaking the ownership transfers explicit.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2qHo3DmhTPz", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/nsIX509CertList.idl", "security/manager/ssl/nsNSSCallbacks.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/nsNSSCertificate.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "53df9fbc528e56deb67566e7e02f4441291cfd77", "parents": ["e1b8647ff08e1b9529d146efb2134c6171c4cdae"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1424300 P1 Gracefully handle when the service worker script cache exists, but is empty. r=edenchuang a=gchang", "files": ["dom/workers/ServiceWorkerScriptCache.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c200bc68074adcc07f4a6ea4c5e825cfd103d0af", "parents": ["53df9fbc528e56deb67566e7e02f4441291cfd77"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1424300 P2 Store response URLs in the service worker script cache. r=edenchuang a=gchang", "files": ["dom/workers/ServiceWorkerScriptCache.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a4c977f0603bb528c01f1d08a41f3641a65197d3", "parents": ["c200bc68074adcc07f4a6ea4c5e825cfd103d0af"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1424300 P3 Add a mochitest verifying we can recover if the script cache is deleted. r=edenchuang a=gchang", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/mochitest.ini", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/test_bad_script_cache.html", "dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/update_worker.sjs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4121dc99f1340ea7998fecbf1a238380e01fb039", "parents": ["a4c977f0603bb528c01f1d08a41f3641a65197d3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1513602892, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8389": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e 0d23f8e3ae8f", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1816982111db7aa87837644882de86672c7ed959", "parents": ["4121dc99f1340ea7998fecbf1a238380e01fb039"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e 0d23f8e3ae8f", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5efea9dc422db6ad123c629d63bce0ba444e966a", "parents": ["1816982111db7aa87837644882de86672c7ed959"], "tags": []}], "date": 1513603250, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8390": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1424300 P3.1 Add a mochitest verifying we can recover if the script cache is deleted: Fix merge conflict. r=bustage-fix a=bustage-fix", "files": ["dom/workers/test/serviceworkers/mochitest.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "44c9c219f7a5849e88433dc1d627f5ddb77c89e3", "parents": ["5efea9dc422db6ad123c629d63bce0ba444e966a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1513603892, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8391": {"changesets": [{"author": "Stephen A Pohl \u003cspohl.mozilla.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1419004: Fix crash when setting plugin process names on macOS 10.13.2. r=mstange a=gchang", "files": ["dom/plugins/ipc/PluginUtilsOSX.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "99e8736d4a20fa1b937346863a95bfac9531e73c", "parents": ["44c9c219f7a5849e88433dc1d627f5ddb77c89e3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1421445 - Don't waste space allocating jit code buffer. r=jandem a=lizzard\n\nWhen computing worst-case alignment padding, we don't take into account\nthe buffer already being partially aligned. This saves one word per\nJitCode buffer allocation.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: ZMwBzp97xy", "files": ["js/src/jit/Ion.cpp", "js/src/jit/IonCode.h", "js/src/jit/Linker.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "59058a3856b731ec0fc2955b11aa3dddb7ebeee4", "parents": ["99e8736d4a20fa1b937346863a95bfac9531e73c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1421445 - Add NOP-slide before JIT code buffers on AMD Bobcat. r=jandem a=lizzard\n\nIn order to try and mitigate crashes on 64-bit FF 57+ on AMD Bobcat\nCPUs, insert NOPs before the JIT code buffers. On earlier versions of\nthese processors, hardware bugs cause crashes to occur in locations\nbefore the JIT code stub. For simplicity, the JitCode* pointer is\nshifted even on machines that are unaffected. With the previous patch\nfixing over allocation, we end up being size-neutral.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4LqBfOzv6Qy", "files": ["js/src/jit/Ion.cpp", "js/src/jit/IonCode.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7fa49bea2cd66581660b4b8af9725a291c5f0249", "parents": ["59058a3856b731ec0fc2955b11aa3dddb7ebeee4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1421445 - Insert UD2 instructions after JitCode. r=jandem a=lizzard\n\nNow that the extra padding is removed, we can end up with data\nimmediately after indirect jumps. For perf reasons, it is recommended to\ninsert a UD2 instruction in this case to prevent CPU decoding garbage.\nThis also works around a Valgrind bug where the tool segfaults in a\nsimilar scenario.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: ESk41VgKjOW", "files": ["js/src/jit/x64/Assembler-x64.cpp", "js/src/jit/x86/MacroAssembler-x86.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "377dba3f7dd64e49b0f98c3f04f66fbca659172c", "parents": ["7fa49bea2cd66581660b4b8af9725a291c5f0249"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Oriol Brufau \u003coriol-bugzilla@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1424617 - Remove text-shadow in webextension badges. r=dao a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: F4axgM8IL7C", "files": ["toolkit/themes/linux/global/toolbarbutton.css", "toolkit/themes/osx/global/toolbarbutton.css", "toolkit/themes/windows/global/toolbarbutton.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1218f89a7b6185f697d74041446ea96034ca2c0a", "parents": ["377dba3f7dd64e49b0f98c3f04f66fbca659172c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1424657: Make IAccessible::accChild handle remote ids for popup windows. r=eeejay a=lizzard\n\nBug 1422201 changed GetIAccessibleFor so it only handles remote ids when called on the root accessible.\nHowever, this breaks webextension popup documents.\nThese popups have their own HWND, so the root accessible of that HWND needs to handle accChild for ids in remote documents within that HWND.\nTherefore, expand the restriction to cover the root accessible of any HWND, not just the main HWND.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 69v4XSeQLcS", "files": ["accessible/windows/msaa/AccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/windows/msaa/AccessibleWrap.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "59d404cb212d5e4f7d4513bd341314da5aef9ead", "parents": ["1218f89a7b6185f697d74041446ea96034ca2c0a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ian Moody \u003cmoz-ian@perix.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414450 - Allow ability to enable legacy extensions in unbranded builds. r=catlee a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JTuIhSKaN7i", "files": ["browser/config/mozconfigs/linux64/add-on-devel", "browser/config/mozconfigs/macosx64/add-on-devel", "browser/config/mozconfigs/win32/add-on-devel", "browser/config/mozconfigs/win64/add-on-devel"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dba0f5124276e6baa5976bccfd579cc9369a828b", "parents": ["59d404cb212d5e4f7d4513bd341314da5aef9ead"], "tags": []}], "date": 1513605750, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8392": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e 9055e2652f5b\nbe -\u003e dbb8369e51c1\ngu-IN -\u003e fb8f81093308\nis -\u003e 1220185af224", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a182f174a460dd728f27f479ac4a626004c46b7a", "parents": ["dba0f5124276e6baa5976bccfd579cc9369a828b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e 9055e2652f5b\nbe -\u003e dbb8369e51c1\nbr -\u003e d0ad6a819572\ngu-IN -\u003e fb8f81093308\nis -\u003e 0372ff75f91b\nkab -\u003e 727baae8980e\nmy -\u003e eee9ab816d7c", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd987effcad4297ab780d7b9c66708f9fdd48303", "parents": ["a182f174a460dd728f27f479ac4a626004c46b7a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1513606795, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8393": {"changesets": [{"author": "Oriol Brufau \u003coriol-bugzilla@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1403536 - Protect all protocol request methods against unsafe objects. r=ochameau a=gchang", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_console.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/new-console-output/test/mochitest/browser_console_dead_objects.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser_console.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/browser_console_dead_objects.js", "devtools/server/actors/object.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_objectgrips-12.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_objectgrips-17.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_objectgrips-21.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini", "devtools/shared/DevToolsUtils.js", "devtools/shared/webconsole/test/test_consoleapi.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c892ce6b1d5a7b4a13e466e5b4064d49c92b57c3", "parents": ["cd987effcad4297ab780d7b9c66708f9fdd48303"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Owen \u003cbobowencode@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1395187: Use STARTF_FORCEOFFFEEDBACK flag when starting Windows child processes to prevent app starting cursor. r=jimm a=lizzard", "files": ["security/sandbox/chromium/sandbox/win/src/broker_services.cc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fd1e2b98664abc89da68d53da72cf57fb69f88aa", "parents": ["c892ce6b1d5a7b4a13e466e5b4064d49c92b57c3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Magnus Melin \u003cmkmelin+mozilla@iki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1411745 - crash for svg linking to mailbox URI. r=smaug a=gchang", "files": ["dom/base/nsDocument.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d16cbfcbb8993d8831b6a0c0c1a7d55db1720e34", "parents": ["fd1e2b98664abc89da68d53da72cf57fb69f88aa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1417300 - store mDecodedAudioDuration before adjusting sample time. r=jya a=gchang\n\nmDecodedAudioDuration should only save unadjusted timestamp, or it would\ncause next adjustment to be incorrect.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7grtYs075p0", "files": ["dom/media/ogg/OggDemuxer.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2c6da9d74cdaea33f7f4d9d1b5574f4bb687e191", "parents": ["d16cbfcbb8993d8831b6a0c0c1a7d55db1720e34"], "tags": []}], "date": 1513615257, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "csabou@mozilla.com"}, "8394": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Tung \u003cshes050117@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1422815 - P1: Fix for failing to get quotaObject unexpectedly. r=bkelly a=gchang\n\nThis patch is for avoiding use quotaObject while it does not exist in Release.\nNote that we sill catch this in Beta and Nightly by the assertion.", "files": ["dom/cache/FileUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3d30fcbdd4073089ccd365b3d3e613f23ef9e33a", "parents": ["2c6da9d74cdaea33f7f4d9d1b5574f4bb687e191"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon 